    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Our Uninsured Children</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Dr Gerald O Franklin letter on Sept 24 article scores states that were unable to spend federal funds granted them to provide poor children with health insurance</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''40 States Forfeit Health Care Funds for Poor Children'' (front page, Sept. 24):</p>
        <p>This is a prime example of why general trust that state and local governments are in a better position to administer certain programs than the federal government is misguided.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''40 States Forfeit Health Care Funds for Poor Children'' (front page, Sept. 24):</p>
        <p>This is a prime example of why general trust that state and local governments are in a better position to administer certain programs than the federal government is misguided.</p>
        <p>The myriad excuses offered by the states for not being able to spend money granted to them are lame and cross party lines. One can only imagine the chaos that would ensue if money for Medicare and Social Security were handled in the same way.</p>
        <p>Stay tuned for the debate about how best to spend government dollars on improving education.</p>
        <p>GERALD O. FRANKLIN, M.D.  Redding, Conn., Sept. 24, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
